The court has ruled that National Speaker Baleka Mbete has the power to decide on a secret ballot, saying that she was wrong to say that a secret ballot vote is not allowed in a motion of no confidence. JOHANNESBURG - The African National Congress in Parliament says that it will defeat the motion of no confidence against President Jacob Zuma after the Constitutional Court made its ruling on a secret ballot vote on the motion on Thursday.The court has ruled that National Speaker Baleka Mbete has the power to decide on a secret ballot, saying that she was wrong to say that a secret ballot vote is not allowed in a motion of no confidence.&quot;We reiterate our long stated position that we will not support the motion of no confidence on President Jacob Zuma by opposition parties. We will defeat this motion of no confidence by the opposition as we have successfully done so in the previous 4 motions tabled in this 5th term of Parliament,&quot; the ANC said in a statement following the ruling.WATCH: Constitutional Court rulingMore to follow.